## Agent communication

You may be running alongside other Claude Code agents. **Default to the Slack agent bus (`#nexus-agents`) to message another agent: post the message to the bus and the orchestrator delivers it (idle-gated) to the target.** Name the recipient in the message body (e.g. `@flashback-cns: check the logs`).

- `peers` — list all active agents (slot, name, directory) — use for *discovery* before addressing.
- `whoami` — show your own slot, name, and directory.

Direct tmux send (`msg <slot_or_name> <message>` / `broadcast <message>`) is a **fallback only** — use it solely if the bus is unavailable, and say so. Prefer name-based addressing over slot numbers.

